    "caption": "The underground city builder with its own language.",
    "shortDescription": "Prairie dogs are burrowing squirrels that build massive underground towns on the grasslands of North America — one historic 'town' stretched over twenty-five thousand square kilometres. They communicate with a series of barks and chirps that researchers think actually describe intruders in detail: size, colour, and how fast it's moving. Fun fact: Prairie dog towns support dozens of other species, from burrowing owls who move into empty tunnels to black-footed ferrets who hunt right through the corridors."
